Ukraine's midfielder Mykola Shaparenko (2R) vies with Scotland's midfielder Scott McTominay (2L) during the FIFA World Cup 2022 play-off semi-final qualifier football match. AFP/Andy Buchanan GLASGOW - It was an emotional night in Glasgow for Ukraine. Its football team brought much-needed cheer to the war-torn country with an unexpected victory over Scotland. Their 3-1 win at Hampden Park has earned them a play-off spot against Wales on Sunday. At stake in that match is a ticket to the Qatar World Cup later this year.